Description: Pottery jar of coarse red-brown siltware, with a shallow pointed base and convex sides narrowing to the (chipped) rim, below which are a double ridge and incised grooves. The exterior is covered with a pale red slip. The shape of the body is slightly irregular.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Tell Dafana, "Qasr", east annex (C), chamber 11
Curator's comments: The Findspot number 11 has been scratched into the side of the vase.
Bibliographic references: Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.93, p.104, p.192, pl.34)
